claude
______

# Disco Limerick

There was a young dancer named Phil,
Whose disco moves gave quite a thrill.
    His hips would sway,
    In a dazzling way,
As he grooved on the dance floor until...

The DJ would spin with such flair,
While strobe lights flashed everywhere.
    With platforms so tall,
    He conquered the hall,
And the ladies all swooned without care.

The mirror ball spun through the night,
Reflecting those colorful lights.
    The beat was so strong,
    They danced all night long,
Till the Saturday fever took flight.

deepseek
________

**Disco Delight**  

There once was a dancer so slick,  
Whose moves made the crowd feel so sick!  
With a shimmering shirt,  
He’d strut and assert,  
No one boogied as bold or as quick!  

The mirror ball spun with a flash,  
As feet hit the floor with a dash.  
With a *thump-thump-thump*,  
And a hip-shaking bump,  
Even grandmas got caught in the bash!  

But alas, when the DJ said "Stop,"  
The groovers all dropped with a flop.  
Yet the beat in their soul  
Kept them out of control—  
Disco just *would not* let them drop!

gemini
______

The disco ball spun, shining bright,
Reflecting the dancers all night.
With flares wide and bold,
Stories untold,
They boogied with all of their might.

The bassline, a rhythmic delight,
Made everyone feel full of sprite.
The Bee Gees would croon,
Beneath the bright moon,
And glitter would gleam in the light.

Though trends may evolve and depart,
Disco remains in the heart.
A groovy sensation,
Across every nation,
Forever a work of pure art.



